<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<activity xml:id="act-planos" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Planos</title>

<statement>
  <image source="png-source/Floor Plan-bedroom_ES.png">
        <shortdescription>Plano de habitación en rectangular con mobiliario</shortdescription>
      </image>
  <p>La imagen muestra el diseño de un plano de una habitación. Discute con tus compañeros:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>¿Qué cosa les gusta del diseño?</li>
    <li>¿Qué cosa cambiarían y por qué?</li>
  </ol>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Sample response: I like that they put the desk by the window because this might help the person focus more if they are working or can enjoy looking outdoors if they want to take a break.</li>
      <li>Sample response: I would move the plants to the other side of the door so that it can open all the way.</li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-actividad-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li> 
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-3-MD-C-5" text="custom">3.MD.C.5</xref>
      </li>
       <li>
        <custom ref="ccss-buildingTowards"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-3-MD-C-7-b" text="custom">3.MD.C.7.b</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to make sense of floor plans. In the launch, students make sense of how different features of the floor plan such as windows, doors, and furniture are visually represented. Students analyze the plan and consider what is usable floor space and where it makes sense to put the furniture. Students may give both aesthetic and practical reasons for furniture placement. This short activity prepares students to make similar considerations in the next activity.</p>
<p>In the synthesis, students work to explain their reasoning and construct viable arguments (MP3).</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Groups of 2</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>Piensen por un par de minutos en lo que les gusta de este diseño. Piensen también en algo que le cambiarían y por qué</q>
      </li>
      <li>1-2 minutes: independent work time</li>
      <li>2-3 minutes: partner discussion</li>
      <li><p>Monitor for students who discuss:</p><ul>
<li>usable floor space</li>
<li>increasing floor space</li>
</ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <postlude> (se pueden mostrar después del enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<postlude component="profesor">

  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Invite a few students to share what they like about the current design and what they would change and why.</li>
      <li><p>Consider asking:</p><ul>
<li>
<q>¿Por que podría ser una buena idea mover las plantas a otro lugar?</q> (When the door is opened, it might bump into the plants. The door can’t be opened all the way.)</li>
<li>
<q>¿Qué otra cosa podríamos reubicar para que sea más fácil moverse por la habitación?</q></li>
</ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Descripción del desarrollo de lenguaje matemático -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="language-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>
      [+++++++++++++++++++++++++]
    </p>
    <p><em>MLR5 Co-Craft Questions.</em> Display the image of the floor plan, and invite students to write a list of possible mathematical questions they could ask about the situation. Invite students to compare their questions, <q><em>¿Qué tienen en común estas preguntas? ¿En qué son diferentes?</em></q> Amplify questions related to comparison and areas of rectangles.</p>
    <p><em>Advances: Reading, Writing</em></p>    
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Estrategias de acceso para estudiantes con discapacidades -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="accesibility-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>
      [+++++++++++++++++++++++]
    </p>
    <p>
      <em>Action and Expression: Provide Access for Physical Action.</em> Provide access to a variety of pre-cut materials to reduce barriers for students who need support with fine motor skills and students who benefit from extra processing time.
    </p>
    <p>
      Supports accessibility for: Fine Motor Skills, Organization, Visual-Spatial Processing
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

</postlude>

</activity>